<H3> <TI>   Condemns Illegal Price Increases </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Condemns Illegal Price Increases </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1105040994 Caracas Union Radio Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 
10 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1105040994 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<FÊP=106> [Report by <PERSON>Fabiola Vecchionacce</PERSON> from the "Union Radio News" </F>
newscast] 
  [Text] President <PERSON>Rafael Caldera</PERSON> attended an event held to 
celebrate the <DATE>50th anniversary of Fedecamaras</DATE> [<ORGANIZATION>Venezuelan 
Federation of Associations and Chambers of Commerce and 
Industry</ORGANIZATION>]. President <PERSON>Rafael Caldera</PERSON> criticized price increases 
of certain products as well as profiteering in the sale of 
dollars, which are acts of corruption that should be fought. 
That was part of <PERSON>Caldera</PERSON>'s speech during the celebration of the 
50th anniversary of <LOCATION>Fedecamaras</LOCATION>. President <PERSON>Caldera</PERSON> pointed out 
that all sectors of society must join Solidarity's efforts so it 
can make progress. 
  Caldera also talked about the importance of opening up 
opportunities for foreign investment by providing greater legal 
guarantees. He said private and public corruption must be 
fought. Let us listen to excerpts of what <PERSON>Caldera</PERSON> said. 
  [Begin Caldera recording] We have seen how the prices of 
certain products have been increased. The Venezuelan people are 
undoubtedly being hurt by this. It is an act of corruption that 
we have to fight. We know that [words indistinct]. That is why 
an atmosphere such as this, with a spirit of friendship and of 
solidarity, can lead us to expect that we can all make an 
effort. Just as the Venezuelan private sector condemns a 
government official who steals the people's money through public 
works that are built, it should also condemn a private sector 
member, who buys dollars to resell them for an undue profit. 
[end recording] 
  In addition, President <PERSON>Caldera</PERSON> agreed with Fedecamaras 
President <PERSON>Edgar Romero Navas</PERSON> that the fight against inflation 
must not be stopped because, according to <PERSON>Romero Navas</PERSON>, the 
country requires a series of changes. <PERSON>Romero Navas</PERSON> also said 
coherence and compromise are needed in the executive cabinet. 
He said our business and political criteria on the handling of 
the country's resources should also be taken into account. 

</TEXT>

