<H3> <TI>   Health, Social Welfare Minister Resigns </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1903002394 Caracas EL GLOBO in Spanish 18 Mar 94 p 46 </F>
<F P=103> PA1903002394 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas EL GLOBO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <FÊP=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<FÊP=106> [Article by <PERSON>Liz Martinez</PERSON>] </F>
  [Text] Health and Social Welfare Minister <PERSON>Vicente Perez 
Davila</PERSON> presented his irrevocable resignation yesterday. Health 
problems related to his gastrointestinal system have forced the 
minister to resign. 
  <PERSON>Perez Davila</PERSON> coordinated the health area of President <PERSON>Rafael 
Caldera</PERSON>'s government and later headed the liaison commission 
with the <ORGANIZATION>Health and Social Welfare Ministry</ORGANIZATION>. 
  In spite of his youth and having a good professional record, 
today <PERSON>Perez Davila</PERSON> is leaving the ministry for health reasons. 
He expressed his regrets to President <PERSON>Rafael Caldera</PERSON>. It was 
learned yesterday morning that <PERSON>Perez Davila</PERSON> sent a letter to the 
president of the Republic in which he explained the reasons for 
his resignation. In that letter he told President <PERSON>Rafael Caldera</PERSON> 
that he is sure the work of the new authorities at the <ORGANIZATION>Health 
and Social Welfare Ministry</ORGANIZATION> will be successful, because the 
persons working in the ministry are highly qualified and 
motivated. 
  President <PERSON>Caldera</PERSON> will now have to appoint a new health and 
social welfare minister, which must be a person highly qualified 
to direct a ministry confronting a serious hospital crisis. 

</TEXT>

