<H3> <TI>   President Caldera on Constitutional Amendments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Caldera on Constitutional Amendments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA1604162794 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 1550 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1604162794 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<FÊP=106> [From "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President <PERSON>Rafael Caldera</PERSON> has emphasized that 
constitutional amendments must include provisions for an 
impeachment referendum, that is, the possibility that people 
could impeach any government official, including the president, 
who fails to perform his duties. He made these statements at the 
