<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<FÊP=106> [From the "Union Radio News"] </F>
  [Text] President <PERSON>Rafael Caldera</PERSON> has indicated that in 
<LOCATION>Venezuela</LOCATION>, there is a high demand for foreign exchange by 
speculators and that his government has been questioned for 
political rather than economic reasons. Caldera stated that an 
abnormal situation prevails in the country but added that his 
government will win the confidence battle. 
  Caldera emphasized the fact that there are currently two 
crises. One is the institutional crisis resulting from the 
trials of former Presidents <PERSON>Jaime Lusinchi</PERSON> and <PERSON>Carlos Andres 
Perez</PERSON> and the transitional government led by <PERSON>Jose Ramon 
Velasquez</PERSON>, which gave public employees a salary increase without 
enough available funds. The other is the economic crisis 
resulting from the intervention involving <ORGANIZATION>Banco Latino</ORGANIZATION>. 

</TEXT>

