<H3> <TI>   Minister Downplays IMF, UN, World Bank Advice </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Downplays IMF, UN, World Bank Advice </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0506201994 Caracas Union Radio Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 
3 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0506201994 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<FÊP=106> [By <PERSON>Vicenter Briceno</PERSON> from the "Union Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Central Information Office Minister <PERSON>Guillermo 
Alvarez Bajares</PERSON> today downplayed the suggestion by (Rutillier 
Orloge), adviser to the <ORGANIZATION>IMF</ORGANIZATION>, the <ORGANIZATION>United Nations</ORGANIZATION>, and the <ORGANIZATION>World 
Bank</ORGANIZATION>, that the government freeze prices, salaries, and the 
exchange rate for two months. 
  <PERSON>Alvarez</PERSON> said the expert's recommendation contradicts the 
economic policy of President <PERSON>Rafael Caldera</PERSON> as well as the 
economic policy of private economic organizations, such as the 
<ORGANIZATION>Higher Institute of Administration Studies</ORGANIZATION>, <ORGANIZATION>Iesa</ORGANIZATION>, and the 
<ORGANIZATION>Venezuelan-American Chamber of Commerce</ORGANIZATION>, Venamcham. The adviser 
participated in the forum: "Post-Sosa Plan Alternatives for 
<LOCATION>Venezuela</LOCATION>," where he said that President <PERSON>Caldera</PERSON> should adopt 
these measures, otherwise, the crisis will deepen and [words 
indistinct] stabilization in a more radical manner. 
  [Begin recording] [<PERSON>Alvarez</PERSON>] That is the center of the 
economic opposition to the current government. It seems that the 
man went [words indistinct] rope at the house of the hanged. 
  [Reporter] [Words indistinct] all economic proposals of.... 
  [<ORGANIZATION>Alvarez</ORGANIZATION>, interrupting] No, quite the opposite; it disagrees 
with sectors of the private economy. 
  [Reporter] I meant the government's economic policy. 
  [<PERSON>Alvarez</PERSON>] The government's economic policy is absolutely 
independent from what <PERSON>Mr.</PERSON> [name indistinct], the <ORGANIZATION>IMF</ORGANIZATION>, <LOCATION>Venamcham</LOCATION>, 
and <ORGANIZATION>Iesa</ORGANIZATION> might say. Absolutely different. 
  [Reporter] [Words indistinct] break from <ORGANIZATION>IMF</ORGANIZATION>? 
  [<PERSON>Alvarez</PERSON>] No, perhaps a break between the <ORGANIZATION>IMF</ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION>Iesa</ORGANIZATION> and 
Venamcham. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

