</HEADER>

<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Cited on `Destabilization Plan' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Cited on `Destabilization Plan' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA0206172394 Caracas Union Radio Network in Spanish 1100 GMT 
2 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA0206172394 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Union Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<FÊP=106> [From the "Union Radio News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President <PERSON>Rafael Caldera</PERSON> has admitted the existence 
of a destabilization plan, as <ORGANIZATION>Defense</ORGANIZATION> Minister <PERSON>Rafael Montero 
Revette</PERSON> had reported to the <ORGANIZATION>Congress</ORGANIZATION>. The president made this 
statement when he participated in the inauguration of the day of 
reflection on constitutional reforms held at the <ORGANIZATION>Catholic 
University</ORGANIZATION> amphitheater. 
  Caldera indicated that measures have been taken on the 
alleged destabilization plan by the corresponding intelligence 
corps and an investigation has been opened on the case. With 
regard to the constitutional reforms, the president said that 
although this is not the solution to the nation's problems it is 
a condition for making the major changes the nation awaits. 

</TEXT>

